HEADWORD: Judaism
<hw>Ju"da*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Juda⟦ium⟧smus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>juda⟦ium⟧sme</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The religious doctrines and rites of the Jews as
enjoined in the laws of Moses, and for many adherents, in the
Talmud.</def> <rj><au>J. S. Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conformity to the Jewish rites and ceremonies; the
practise of Judaism{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The adherents of Judaism{1} collectively;
jewry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Judaist</ent>⟦br⟧
